item.title: Compile!
item.dc:creator: @orcashark orcashark
item.description:
@orcashark wrote:

well, its most likely your jdk, and ill explain you how to set it. ok first, go to your compiler, right click it and click edit, it will say “Jdk 1.6.0.(unknown)” now, were going to find out what jdk you have, so go to…
My Computer > Local disc c > Java
and there it should say JDK and JRE, next to the JDK it will have a 2 digit number (has to be aboce 10 for compiler to work i believe) so, whatever those 2 numbers are, replace them with the last 2 numbers on your compiler. once thats dont, click exit, yes and it should work. if i made any mistakes please post here and ill check myself
